Master Deep Learning with R ? in Just 2 Days

*Deep Learning using R (DLUR01)* is a practical, instructor-led online
course designed to take you from the foundations of neural networks to
building modern deep-learning models in R. Ideal for researchers, analysts,
and data scientists, this workshop blends essential theory with hands-on
implementation.
What You Will Learn

   -

   The biological and mathematical foundations of neural networks, from
   perceptrons to deep multilayer architectures.
   -

   How to train neural networks using backpropagation, gradient descent,
   stochastic gradient descent, Adam, regularisation, and other optimization
   strategies.
   -

   How to implement working models in R, including multilayer perceptrons
   for tabular data, convolutional neural networks for image classification,
   and transformer-style language models for text.
   -

   How to build a minimal GPT-style model from scratch, including
   tokenisation, embeddings, attention mechanisms, and text generation.
   -

   How to select appropriate architectures (MLP, CNN, transformer) based on
   data characteristics and project goals.

Why This Course Stands Out

   -

   Two intensive days (6 hours per day) combining theory, guided coding,
   and real-data examples.
   -

   Live online course with full access to recordings after each session.
   -

   Option to work with your own data during practical segments.
   -

   Continued support and access to materials for 30 days following the
   course.

Who Should Attend

   -

   Researchers and data scientists who use R and want to extend their
   skills into deep learning for images, text, or complex datasets.
   -

   Professionals comfortable with R and basic statistical and data-handling
   concepts who are new to neural networks but want to build practical,
   working models.
   -

   Anyone seeking to learn modern deep-learning methods without needing to
   switch programming languages.

